oc:kn_1b01c72d a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing between paretoset library and manual implementation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the paretoset library for production code over manual implementations; manual dominance checks are O(n²) and error-prone." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The library handles edge cases, is optimized, and reduces bugs" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a79240c8 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing or verifying Pareto dominance checks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Pareto dominance requires that point A is at least as good as B in ALL objectives AND strictly better in at least ONE objective; both conditions must hold." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect dominance logic yields wrong Pareto frontiers and bad optimization decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c37a88d3 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting or acting on Pareto-optimal results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "There is no single best solution on the Pareto frontier — all Pareto-optimal points represent equally valid trade-offs; final selection requires stakeholder preference." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Assuming a single best point defeats the purpose of multi-objective optimization" .

